  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (7398b65 2023-03-30T00:05:52.75238Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n> Calls to mocked addresses may revert if there is no code on the address. \r\n\r\nHowever there is a [check](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/cbb82940dab93252fca957749cb24a673829cc6e/evm/src/executor/inspector/cheatcodes/expect.rs#L349) for only in MockCall0.\r\n\r\nI believe the same should also be done for `MockCall1`, `MockCallRevert0`, `MockCallRevert1` as well.",
